{
  "texts": [
    "Technological advancements in biomaterial's production are scrutinized for their potential to drive broader adoption, while a comprehensive analysis of the benefits and risks associated with biomaterials use encompasses health, safety, and environmental sustainability considerations.",
    "The review concludes by presenting a forward-looking perspective, emphasizing opportunities and obstacles for increased adoption, and providing recommendations for future research and action.",
    "Overall, this review aspires to offer valuable insights into the pivotal role of biomaterials in shaping a more sustainable and resilient future for the construction industry.",
    "Biomaterials have emerged as a transformative and sustainable solution in the construction industry, offering a promising alternative to conventional materials (Liu et al. 2022c).",
    "Derived from renewable resources, biomaterials leverage the inherent properties of nature to create innovative and eco-conscious building materials (Alemu et al. 2022)."
  ]
}